body:
@deroneriksson 
1. Could you please add the following lines from Quickstart guide: _The standalone release packages all required libraries into a single distribution file. In standalone mode, all operations occur on a single node in a non-Hadoop environment. Standalone mode is not appropriate for large datasets._
2. As part of this PR or a new one, could you modify the java invocation in `.sh` and `.bat` scripts to accept JVM size as configuration parameters -- with a default value of `4g` (or `2g`)?  This would give users a bit of flexibility when they are prototyping on their laptops. You could also mention a couple of lines reg. this setting in readme.txt.

@shirisht 
(1) Updated to integrate that information into the readme.
(2) Created SYSTEMML-486 to do JVM size in a separate PR.

@dusenberrymw 
Updated readme.txt to README.txt. Modified standalone.xml accordingly.

@mboehm7 
Updated MAPREDUCE to MR.

Might also be nice to do something like rename MRConfigurationNames to MRProp. Also, might be nice to remove the INVALID settings of the public statics so that they can be made public static finals since they are being set in the static initialization block.
